Verified Purchase
I have tried other keyboards, and I come back to this one. I have an original one from when they 1st came out and it just will not quit. It is slightly larger than this one, but this, the keys are easy to push, not to noisy, the wrist pad is soft. They only thing that it needs are feet on the back. I prefer to have my keyboard raised just a bit in the back for a little bit more of a slant, this one does not have that, so I just lean it up on my laptop and that works just fine. Overall, I would recommend this keyboard, plug and play, no software or drivers to install. It is wired, but if that doesn't bother you, it is a good value, nice keyboard.
